text: Hi Eden: You may certainly work through the graphical user interface (GUI) with the icons. You can also try deleting the files in the command line terminal using the *rm* command to first delete individual files within a directory (folder) and then to use the *rmdir* command to remove the folder. You can also use the *rm -rf* command to *f*orce the *r*ecursive removal of both the folders and files within those folders. For all of these, you need to supply the filename or folder name you attempting to delete.
